<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1945,2011]" lastBlockId="4.[151,1437,152,498]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="5" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,383,1945,1971]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Pygofer (
<figureCitation box="[499,585,1945,1971]" captionStart="FIGURES 14 – 17. C" captionStartId="5.[151,269,1266,1290]" captionTargetBox="[336,1231,193,1226]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[325,1259,181,1243]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 14 – 17. C hromagallia carvalhoi sp. nov. Male: (14) genital capsule, lateral view; (15) subgenital plates, ventral view; (16) style, dorsal view; (17) aedeagus, connective, and style, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/181696/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
Fig. 
<number box="[553,585,1945,1971]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="14.0">14</number>
</figureCitation>
), in lateral view, short, with posterior portion subtriangular and posterior margin with lobe directed inward. Subgenital plates (
<figureCitation box="[778,865,1985,2011]" captionStart="FIGURES 14 – 17. C" captionStartId="5.[151,269,1266,1290]" captionTargetBox="[336,1231,193,1226]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[325,1259,181,1243]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 14 – 17. C hromagallia carvalhoi sp. nov. Male: (14) genital capsule, lateral view; (15) subgenital plates, ventral view; (16) style, dorsal view; (17) aedeagus, connective, and style, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/181696/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
Fig. 
<number box="[834,865,1985,2011]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="15.0">15</number>
</figureCitation>
), in ventral view, small, with distal half triangular, fused to each other only at basal half, basal portion with narrow median area less sclerotized; in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[225,310,192,218]" captionStart="FIGURES 14 – 17. C" captionStartId="5.[151,269,1266,1290]" captionTargetBox="[336,1231,193,1226]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[325,1259,181,1243]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 14 – 17. C hromagallia carvalhoi sp. nov. Male: (14) genital capsule, lateral view; (15) subgenital plates, ventral view; (16) style, dorsal view; (17) aedeagus, connective, and style, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/181696/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
Fig. 
<number box="[280,310,192,218]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="14.0">14</number>
</figureCitation>
) extending posteriorly well beyond pygofer apex; surface with scattered setae, dorsoapical surface with longer setae. Styles (
<figureCitation box="[508,593,232,258]" captionStart="FIGURES 14 – 17. C" captionStartId="5.[151,269,1266,1290]" captionTargetBox="[336,1231,193,1226]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[325,1259,181,1243]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 14 – 17. C hromagallia carvalhoi sp. nov. Male: (14) genital capsule, lateral view; (15) subgenital plates, ventral view; (16) style, dorsal view; (17) aedeagus, connective, and style, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/181696/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
Fig. 
<number box="[562,593,232,258]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="16.0">16</number>
</figureCitation>
), in dorsal view, slender, fork well developed and curved outward; style shaft (
<figureCitation box="[224,310,272,298]" captionStart="FIGURES 14 – 17. C" captionStartId="5.[151,269,1266,1290]" captionTargetBox="[336,1231,193,1226]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[325,1259,181,1243]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 14 – 17. C hromagallia carvalhoi sp. nov. Male: (14) genital capsule, lateral view; (15) subgenital plates, ventral view; (16) style, dorsal view; (17) aedeagus, connective, and style, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/181696/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
Fig. 
<number box="[280,310,272,298]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="16.0">16</number>
</figureCitation>
) with small projection on inner margin for articulation with connective. Connective, in anterior view, forming an inverted “T”, not fused with aedeagal base. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[1000,1085,312,338]" captionStart="FIGURES 14 – 17. C" captionStartId="5.[151,269,1266,1290]" captionTargetBox="[336,1231,193,1226]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[325,1259,181,1243]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 14 – 17. C hromagallia carvalhoi sp. nov. Male: (14) genital capsule, lateral view; (15) subgenital plates, ventral view; (16) style, dorsal view; (17) aedeagus, connective, and style, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/181696/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
Fig. 
<number box="[1055,1085,312,338]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="17.0">17</number>
</figureCitation>
) symmetrical; shaft, in lateral view, directed anteriorly on basal portion, then strongly curved posterodorsally, remaining area straight, directed ventrally and narrowed towards apex; curved portion distinctly lobed; apex slightly spiralized. Membrane IX–X with pair of small, slender processes (
<figureCitation box="[745,833,432,458]" captionStart="FIGURES 14 – 17. C" captionStartId="5.[151,269,1266,1290]" captionTargetBox="[336,1231,193,1226]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[325,1259,181,1243]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 14 – 17. C hromagallia carvalhoi sp. nov. Male: (14) genital capsule, lateral view; (15) subgenital plates, ventral view; (16) style, dorsal view; (17) aedeagus, connective, and style, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/181696/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
Fig. 
<number box="[800,833,432,458]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="14.0">14</number>
</figureCitation>
). Anal tube (
<figureCitation box="[986,1073,432,458]" captionStart="FIGURES 14 – 17. C" captionStartId="5.[151,269,1266,1290]" captionTargetBox="[336,1231,193,1226]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[325,1259,181,1243]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 14 – 17. C hromagallia carvalhoi sp. nov. Male: (14) genital capsule, lateral view; (15) subgenital plates, ventral view; (16) style, dorsal view; (17) aedeagus, connective, and style, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/181696/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
Fig. 
<number box="[1041,1073,432,458]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="14.0">14</number>
</figureCitation>
), in lateral view, with segment X
</paragraph>
